<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D47CD325AB93CF8E6" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[656,839,1873,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="17 - 30" refId="ref14740" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2011) Descriptions of Neboissomina, new genus and 6 new species of Ecnomidae from Australia (Trichoptera). Zootaxa, 2736 (1), 17 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2736.1.2" type="journal article" year="2011">
Cartwright 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF0682D464D325AB93CF8E6" box="[784,839,1873,1899]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10794" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" unit="in" value="2011.0">2011</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in possessing inferior appendages which are fused to form a single large sub-rectangular plate, but it is distinguished by the three, minute, acute projections apicolaterally and apicomesally on each inferior appendage, in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF0682F459A32B6BBE4FE90" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="290" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682E459A32B6BF00FECC" blockId="5.[151,1437,1549,2008]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="289" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D459A32B6BBE0F85A" bold="true" box="[199,411,1981,2007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Description, male</emphasis>
. Spur formula: 3:4:4. Head, body, and wings light brown, abdomen paler ventrally; wings (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E45FD359CBA98FF3F" box="[160,227,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF3682E4499359CB846FF3C" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2011" box="[452,573,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Neboissomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jardinei">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E4499359CB846FF3C" box="[452,573,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">N. jardinei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF3682E4716359CB97CFF3C" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[587,775,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" pagination="17 - 30" refId="ref14740" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2011) Descriptions of Neboissomina, new genus and 6 new species of Ecnomidae from Australia (Trichoptera). Zootaxa, 2736 (1), 17 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2736.1.2" type="journal article" year="2011">Cartwright 2011</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2), length of each forewing: male 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF3682E41E6359CBF3FFF3C" box="[1211,1348,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.3">2.3–3.1 mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF3682E45CA35B0BB58FF58" box="[151,291,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.1 mm</quantity>
, length about 3.0 times width; length of each hind wing 3.2–3.3 times width. Wing venation: Each forewing with forks 2, 3, 4, and 5 present; fork 2 sessile, length about 1.5 times length of fork 3; fork 3 with length of fork about twice length of footstalk, fork 4 about 0.8 times length of fork 3, fork 5 about 1.6–1.7 times length of fork 4. Hind wings each with forks 2, 3, and 5 present; fork 2 sessile, its length about 1.7 times length of fork 3.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2171A4FFF3682E45CA333ABBC0F973" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" startId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" targetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF3682E45CA333ABBC0F973" blockId="6.[151,1437,1585,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E45CA333ABB32F9C7" bold="true" box="[151,329,1585,1610]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">FIGURES 6–12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF3682E440D3339BBBEF9C7" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1903" box="[336,453,1586,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ecnomidae</taxonomicName>
. Figures 6–9, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF3682E47053339B92FF9C7" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[600,852,1586,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Neboissomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topendica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E47053339B92FF9C7" box="[600,852,1586,1610]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Neboissomina topendica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E46063339B9D6F9C7" bold="true" box="[859,941,1586,1610]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFF3682E46063339B9D6F9C7" box="[859,941,1586,1610]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF3682E4625335DBE2BF9E3" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[888,1104,1622,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamoides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E4625335DBE2BF9E3" box="[888,1104,1622,1646]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Wellsomina tamoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E4104335DBED0F9E3" bold="true" box="[1113,1195,1622,1646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFF3682E4104335DBED0F9E3" box="[1113,1195,1622,1646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF3682F459A3227B9A2FF74" blockId="6.[151,1437,1836,2042]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="290" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF3682E459A3227BB73F8CB" box="[199,264,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Male.</emphasis>
Tergum X membranous, with pair of long, slender dorsal sclerotized processes converging near middle and diverging posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E449F325BB87CF8E7" box="[450,519,1872,1898]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Superior appendages short and robust (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E468E325BBE43F8E7" box="[979,1080,1872,1898]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Figs 7, 9</figureCitation>
), in lateral view appearing subrectangular, very slightly tapered posteriorly, length about 2.8 times width, apices slightly rounded (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E41B8327FBF53F803" box="[1253,1320,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view slightly dilated in posterior third (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E47143293B8F7F83F" box="[585,652,1944,1970]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); pair of long, slender curved processes (mesal processes of tergum X) ventral to superior appendages. Phallus simple, tube-like (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E464632B7B906F85B" box="[795,893,1980,2006]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) with elongate, slender process partly embedded and emergent posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E449D32EBB87DF877" box="[448,518,2016,2042]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages slightly longer than superior appendages, fused (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF3682E407532EBBFF4F877" box="[1320,1423,2016,2042]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">Figs 7–9</figureCitation>
), in ventral view large, subrectangular shield, truncate posteriorly, length about 1.5 times width, with acute apicolateral corners and acute apicomesal projection (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F47FD35B0B89EFF58" box="[672,741,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), in lateral view robust, tapered basally, very slightly tapered posteriorly, appearing sub-trapezoidal, length about 3 times width (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F46DA35D4B9B0FF74" box="[903,971,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A3408BBE4FE90" blockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" box="[199,415,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A3408BB58FE90" box="[199,291,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF2682F459A342CBF55FECC" box="[199,1326,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A342CBF55FECC" blockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" box="[199,1326,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A342CBB35FECC" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Etymology.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F4408342CBBB2FECC" box="[341,457,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Topendica</emphasis>
—based on the colloquial regional name for the locality (Top End of the NT).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF2682F459A3440BE30FE04" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A3440BE30FE04" blockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A3440BB40FEE8" bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Remarks.</emphasis>
At least thirty males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF2682F47123440B8A4FEE8" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[591,735,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Neboissomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topendica">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F47123440B8A4FEE8" box="[591,735,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">N. topendica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected from 3 localities in the Top End (latitude range 12.80– 
<geoCoordinate id="EE6A47EBFFF2682F44773465BBF0FE04" box="[298,395,366,393]" degrees="14.59" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" precision="555" value="-14.59">14.59 °S</geoCoordinate>
), including sites in Kakadu NP and in the greater Darwin area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
